      "summary": ": Monday 20th July Home Basin, Open Saddle Basin, Open Matukituki Basin, Closed Summit Slopes, Open Motatapu Chutes, Closed Sundance, Closed Backcountry Access, Open Skinning Access, Open Good morning, and welcome to the new week! We're looking at a mostly fine day up the mountain — a great way to kick things off. Our grooming team has been out overnight, and Triple Treat and upper Main Street are groomed up and looking sharp for first tracks. And with cool temps, the Snowmakers have been working hard right through the night refreshing and building our main trails. Conditions are holding nicely across the mountain, albeit thin in spots. Get on up here and make the most of the fine weather while it lasts ~ there is a storm coming this week which holds the promise of more snow on the way! See you up here for a great day!",
